    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "2b771b85_846a56cd",
        "filename": "common/testing/assertions/error_tests.go",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 36,
      "author": {
        "id": 1001907
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-12-13T22:42:01Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I would just make ShouldContainErr require a value.\n\nNote that go is tricky wrt error and MultiError and nil. For example https://play.golang.org/p/gHHZLoxwXz5 prints \u0027false\u0027.\n\nI think it would make sense for:\n\n    So(MultiError{}, ShouldContainErr, nil)\n    So(MultiError{nil}, ShouldContainErr, nil)\n\nTo unique messages like \"Hey! You have an empty MultiErrror! This is almost always wrong, and this should be `error(nil)` instead!\"\n\nor something like that.",
      "parentUuid": "93e5f3a0_841ee63c",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 34,
        "startChar": 1,
        "endLine": 36,
        "endChar": 2
      },
      "revId": "ba695fe308d62394091e740e80806d2e35929ab8",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "ed700dcd_d6b2e1cc",
        "filename": "common/testing/assertions/error_tests.go",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 36,
      "author": {
        "id": 1003211
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-12-13T22:50:53Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I\u0027m not sure an empty MultiError is wrong. If I were writing code where I accumulated errors into a MultiError, I\u0027d expect to be able to return an empty MultiError and have it be treated as \"no errors occurred\", rather than having to do an extra check at the end for \"if len(errs) \u003d\u003d 0 { return nil }\".\n\nThough I agree that MultiError{nil} is almost certainly wrong (open question on the comment below).",
      "parentUuid": "2b771b85_846a56cd",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 34,
        "startChar": 1,
        "endLine": 36,
        "endChar": 2
      },
      "revId": "ba695fe308d62394091e740e80806d2e35929ab8",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "830d48e7_399ea04e",
        "filename": "common/testing/assertions/error_tests.go",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 36,
      "author": {
        "id": 1003211
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-12-13T23:05:27Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Actually MultiError semantics seem to handle contained nils specifically. A MultiError ignores its nil errors when figuring how many errors there are:\nhttps://godoc.org/go.chromium.org/luci/common/errors#MultiError.Summary\n\nWhich means that MultiError{nil} is actually valid, and ShouldContainErr(MultiError{nil}, nil) should probably succeed as normal. It\u0027s perhaps equivalent to ShouldContain([]errors{nil}, nil). I\u0027d probably expect that to succeed even if it doesn\u0027t really make sense why I have a nil error in a slice of errors.",
      "parentUuid": "ed700dcd_d6b2e1cc",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 34,
        "startChar": 1,
        "endLine": 36,
        "endChar": 2
      },
      "revId": "ba695fe308d62394091e740e80806d2e35929ab8",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "0e9949d5_ff8da861",
        "filename": "common/testing/assertions/error_tests.go",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 36,
      "author": {
        "id": 1001907
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-12-13T23:24:43Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "All I\u0027m saying is that because `error` is an interface, doing the naive thing:\n\n    func Something() error {\n      var err MultiError   // it\u0027s nil!\n      // code, nothing appends to err\n      return err           // still a nil MultiError!\n    }\n\n    ...\n  \n    func InnocentBystander() error {\n      if err :\u003d Something(); err !\u003d nil {\n         // oops, err isn\u0027t nil here! It\u0027s a non-nil `error` interface\n         // which contains a nil MultiError.\n         return err\n      }\n      ...\n    }\n\nWill always be wrong. Maybe this assertion is the wrong place to catch this, though, but I sort of feel like it should have an opinion.",
      "parentUuid": "830d48e7_399ea04e",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 34,
        "startChar": 1,
        "endLine": 36,
        "endChar": 2
      },
      "revId": "ba695fe308d62394091e740e80806d2e35929ab8",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "6c4ff338_2634af07",
        "filename": "common/testing/assertions/error_tests.go",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 36,
      "author": {
        "id": 1003211
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-12-13T23:47:46Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "The only successful assertion using this function and your code would be So(Something(), ShouldContainErr). It correctly detects that Something() returned an empty MultiError (in patchset 2, not this patchset).\n\nI\u0027m not sure it\u0027s this function\u0027s concern that Something() is returning something you probably don\u0027t want in your code.\n\nShould succeed:\nSo(Something(), ShouldContainErr) // check that the MultiError is empty\n\nShould fail:\nSo(Something(), ShouldContainErr, nil) // check that the MultiError contains a nil",
      "parentUuid": "0e9949d5_ff8da861",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 34,
        "startChar": 1,
        "endLine": 36,
        "endChar": 2
      },
      "revId": "ba695fe308d62394091e740e80806d2e35929ab8",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
